def findContestMatch(n):
    matches = [str(i) for i in range(1, n + 1)]

    while n > 1:
        for i in range(n // 2):
            matches[i] = "(" + matches[i] + "," + matches[n - 1 - i] + ")"
        n //= 2

    return matches[0]
```


    This algorithm initializes an array of matches with `n` elements, each representing a team. It then generates one half of the final contest matches using a while loop. During each iteration of the while loop, for every pair of teams `i` and `n - 1 - i`, we form a new match by creating a string with the format `(team1,team2)` and store it in the matches array. With each iteration, we divide the number of matches by 2, which eventually gives us the final contest match at the first index of the matches array.

